'''Dominik Kotarski''' ({{IPA|hr|dôminik kôtarskiː, domǐ-}};<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hjp.znanje.hr/index.php?show=search_by_id&id=f1ZhWhc%3D|title=Dȍminik|quote=Dȍminik (Domìnik)|website=Hrvatski jezični portal|accessdate=28 November 2018|language=sh}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://hjp.znanje.hr/index.php?show=search_by_id&id=elljUBc%3D|title=kȍtār|quote=Kȍtarskī|website=Hrvatski jezični portal|accessdate=28 November 2018|language=sh}}</ref> born 10 February 2000) is a Croatian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Danish Superliga]] club [[F.C. Copenhagen|Copenhagen]] and the [[Croatia national football team|Croatia national team]].

==Club career==
===Ajax===
Growing up in [[Brestovec Orehovički]], Kotarski started training with his local club NK Tondach Bedekovčina at the age of 6.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Zrinšćak |first=Tomislav |date=2025-06-10 |title=VELIKI TRANSFER: Dominik Kotarski potpisao za moćni Ajax |url=https://www.zagorje.com/clanak/vijesti/veliki-transfer-dominik-kotarski-potpisao-za-mocni-ajax |access-date=2025-06-09 |website=Zagorje.com |language=hr}}</ref> After impressing, he moved to [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]]'s academy in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zagorje.com/clanak/vijesti/veliki-transfer-dominik-kotarski-potpisao-za-mocni-ajax|title=VELIKI TRANSFER: Dominik Kotarski potpisao za moćni Ajax|first=Metro m.k. |last=www.virtuabit.hr|date=8 September 2023 |publisher=}}</ref> On 7 July 2017, he signed his first professional contract with [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] but had to wait until he turned 18 to officially sign with the club, and he is contracted until 30 June 2023.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ajax.nl/streams/actueel/ajax-contracteert-dominik-kotarski.htm|title=Ajax contracteert Dominik Kotarski|publisher=}}</ref>

Kotarski made his professional debut for Jong Ajax in a 3–0 [[Eerste Divisie]] loss to [[Jong PSV]] on 30 March 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nl.soccerway.com/matches/2018/03/30/netherlands/eerste-divisie/jong-ajax/jong-psv/2463498/|title=Jong Ajax vs. Jong PSV – 30 maart 2018 – Soccerway|website=nl.soccerway.com}}</ref> Kotarski was made the third keeper of the first team ahead of the [[2018–19 Eredivisie]] season. Due to good health of first and second choice keepers [[André Onana]] and [[Kostas Lamprou]], he continued to ply his trade with the reserves.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ajaxshowtime.com/article/hoofdnieuws/110694/ajax-breekt-contract-keeper-kotarski-open|title=Ajax breekt contract van derde keeper Kotarski open|website=AjaxShowtime|date=16 February 2018|access-date=13 May 2019|archive-date=13 May 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190513094120/http://www.ajaxshowtime.com/article/hoofdnieuws/110694/ajax-breekt-contract-keeper-kotarski-open|url-status=dead}}</ref>

====Gorica (loan)====
On 16 June 2021 it was announced that Kotarski would be loaned to [[HNK Gorica]] on a season-long loan spell, competing in the [[Croatian First Football League|1. HNL]], the top-tier of professional football in his native Croatia.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraaf.nl/sport/989868933/ajax-verhuurt-keeper-dominik-kotarski|title=HNK Gorica nieuwe club - Ajax verhuurt keeper Dominik Kotarski|date=15 June 2021 |publisher=De Telegraaf}}</ref> He featured 24 times in the league and 4 times in the [[Croatian Football Cup|cup]], keeping a clean sheet in 8 of those matches.

===PAOK===
Οn 27 June 2022, Kotarski signed a four-year contract with Greek club [[PAOK FC|PAOK]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://talentabout.gr/2022/06/o-agiax-anoixe-ton-dromo-tou-paok-gia-ton-kotarski-photo/|title=Ο Άγιαξ άνοιξε τον δρόμο του ΠΑΟΚ για τον Κοτάρσκι!|date=17 June 2022|publisher=talentabout.gr|access-date=20 June 2022|archive-date=7 July 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220707081507/https://talentabout.gr/2022/06/o-agiax-anoixe-ton-dromo-tou-paok-gia-ton-kotarski-photo/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

===FC Copenhagen===
On 9 July 2025, [[Danish Superliga]] club [[F.C. Copenhagen]] announced the signing of Kotarski on a five-year deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fck.dk/nyhed/fc-koebenhavn-koeber-dominik-kotarski-fra-paok-fc|title=FC København køber Dominik Kotarski fra PAOK FC|trans-title=FC København buys Dominik Kotarski from PAOK FC|publisher=FC Copenhagen|date=9 July 2025|access-date=24 July 2025|language=da}}</ref>

==International career==
Kotarski is a youth international for Croatia, and was the standout player for the [[Croatia national under-17 football team|Croatia U17]]s at the [[2017 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/nogomet/mlada-zvijezda-potpisala-za-velikana-i-vec-sada-napusta-maksimir-jedan-od-najvecih-inzisitrao-na-njegovom-dolasku-njegovo-iskustvo-je-neprocjenjivo/7002141/|title=MLADA ZVIJEZDA POTPISALA ZA VELIKANA I VEĆ SADA NAPUŠTA MAKSIMIR Jedan od najvećih inzisitrao na njegovom dolasku: 'Njegovo iskustvo je neprocjenjivo'|date=5 February 2018 |publisher=}}</ref>

On 31 October 2022, Kotarski was named in [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]]'s preliminary 34-man squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/sp-2022/prosireni-popis-zlatka-dalica-za-svjetsko-prvenstvo---749474.html |title=Dalić objavio prošireni popis za Svjetsko prvenstvo: Evo tko ima šansu putovati u Katar |website=Gol.hr |date=2022-10-31 |access-date=2022-12-21 |language=hr}}</ref> but did not make the [[2022 FIFA World Cup squads#Croatia|final 26]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vecernji.hr/sport/uzivo-od-11-sati-zlatko-dalic-objavljuje-konacni-popis-igraca-za-sp-1632085 |title=Zlatko Dalić objavio popis igrača za SP, ovo su 26 imena koje vodi u Katar |website=Večernji list |date=2022-11-09 |access-date=2022-12-21 |language=hr}}</ref>

He made his debut on 26 March 2024 in a friendly against Egypt, substituting another debutant [[Nediljko Labrović]] at half-time.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/701261/croatia-egypt|title=Egypt v Croatia game report|date=26 March 2024}}</ref>

